.edu/rutgers-lib/66095/"}, {"speaker": "Patricia Willard", "relation": "in music group with", "confidence": 0.95, "evidence": "He wrote himself, some stuff and I arranged some things for the band.", "doc_title": "61531_Juan Tizol oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/61531/"}, {"speaker": "Louie Bellson", "relation": "in music group with", "confidence": 0.9, "evidence": "I found after working with the band I discovered in a very short time that you could have Ellington’s band play an arrangement... Carney, Willie Smith, Johnny Hodges, Paul Gonsalves, Jimmy Hamilton, Clark Terry, Juan Tizol, Lawrence Brown, Tricky Sam.", "doc_title": "Louie Bellson interviewed by Monk Rowe, Sarasota, Florida, April 12, 1996", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/louie-bellson-interviewed-monk-rowe-sarasota-florida-april-12-1996"}, {"speaker": "Tom Whaley", "relation": "in music group with", "confidence": 0.9, "evidence": "[INTERVIEWER] You know, in observing Duke's band... perhaps in later years, the clarinet player that's down in the West Indies now. >> [INTERVIEWEE] Jimmy Hamilton.", "doc_title": "68163_Tom Whaley oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/68163/"}]}